cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about domain adaptation for neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach that involves learning domain-aware feature embeddings, which is a machine learning technique. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions using back translation, which is a common technique in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE), making these sub-categories possible as well.
